The 2-m Liverpool Telescope automatically began observing Swift GRB 
180512A (Deich et al. GCN 22710) on May 12, 22:07:15 UT (5.5 minutes 
since the GRB) with the RINGO3 polarimeter and the IO:O camera in the 
SDSS-R filter. Within the enhanced XRT error circle (Evans et al. GCN 
22715) we do not detect any optical counterpart down to the following 
magnitude:

